Rain, lightning over Reno-Sparks area

by News 4-Fox 11 Digital Team

Thu, September 5th 2019 at 8:29 PM
Updated Thu, September 5th 2019 at 10:08 PM
12
VIEW ALL PHOTOS
Thunder storm over Reno Photo: Rebecca and Marlee Comba

    TOPICS:

    Geography Of NevadaGeography of the United StatesNevadaRegions Of The United StatesRenoReno, NV Metropolitan Statistical AreaReno, NevadaReno–Sparks Metropolitan Area

RENO, Nev. (News 4-Fox 11) — A strong thunderstorm is moving through the Reno-Sparks area this evening.

More than 2,900 people were without power in Washoe County. Power has been restored to most people in the area, according to NV Energy's website.

Are you seeing any lighting this evening? Send us your photos and videos to Chimein for a chance to be featured online and on air!
